condition.narrative: (Schedule 2.I.A.1 - amended) The Recipient shall maintain, until completion of the Project, a Project Steering Committee, withterms of reference, mandate, resources and composition satisfactory to the Association. The Project Steering Committee shall be:(a) chaired by the Minister of Petroleum and-Energy, (b) composed of representatives of the Recipient's Ministry of Finance andBudget, Ministry of Economy, Plan and Co-operation, Ministry of Environment and Sustainable Development, Ministry of Fisheries andMaritime Economy and Ministry of Petroleum and Energy, and representatives of PETROSEN and COS-Petrogaz, and ( c) responsible forinter alia (i) providing strategic orientation for the Project and supervising its implementation; (ii) reviewing and adopting theAnnual Work Plan in accordance with Section I.D. of this Schedule; and (iii) formulating recommendations and proposals tofacilitate Project implementation

(Schedule 2.I.B.1) The Recipient shall: (i) through PETROSEN, carry out the Project in accordance with PETROSEN Project Manual;(ii) through GES-PETROGAZ, shall adopt, not later than six (6) months after the Effective Date, a revised Project Manualsatisfactory to the Association; and (iii) not amend, abrogate, waive or permit to be amended, abrogated or waived, theaforementioned Project Manual, or any provision thereof, without the prior written consent of the Association.

(Schedule 2.I.E.1) The Recipient shall ensure that a Master Plan for Oil and Gas Development is prepared in accordance with termsof reference approved by the Association. If the Master Plan for Oil and Gas Development is finalized during Projectimplementation, the Recipient shall prepare a Strategic Environmental and Social Assessment of the oil and gas sector acceptable tothe Association.

(Schedule 2.II.B.4) The Recipient shall by not later than six (6) months after the Effective Date: (i) select one external auditorand one internal auditor, both with qualifications satisfactory to the Association; and (ii) recruit an accountant pursuant totermsof reference and with qualifications and experience satisfactory to the Association.
